<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5710] ActiveMQConnection cleanup should not close the connection on the broker</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5710</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As the spec says&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.oracle.com/javaee/6/api/javax/resource/spi/ManagedConnection.html#cleanup(&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://docs.oracle.com/javaee/6/api/javax/resource/spi/ManagedConnection.html#cleanup(&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The cleanup of ManagedConnection instance resets its client specific state and prepares the connection to be put back in to a connection pool. The cleanup method should not cause resource adapter to close the physical pipe and reclaim system resources associated with the physical connection.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should not send RemoveInfo on cleanup, but just clean client side state. The result of &quot;closing&quot; a connection on cleanup is that connection will not be cached when using XA transactions, causing high CPU usage on the broker.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
